    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Running `:difft` on files that are very large (>1 million lines in my specific case) takes a very long time to finish. During that time, Neovim is unusable. I don't think any diff algorithm could handle such large files in a reasonable amount of time, so it would be nice to be able to interrupt `:difft` with `<C-c>`.",
